The single source of truth for how to work in this repository is **`AGENTS.md`**
at the repo root. Read it first and follow it.

Non-negotiables (full detail in `AGENTS.md`):

- Never modify the write-protected substrate files listed in `AGENTS.md` ┬ž0.
- Gate every change with `npm run agent:check`; never weaken a test to pass it.
- Keep `src/engine`, `src/physics`, `src/net`, and `src/persistence` pure (no DOM,
  sockets, timers, or unseeded `Math.random` in test-reachable paths).
- Use Conventional Commits; keep changes small and focused.
